OL,7,FHe continued: "The prosecution say
OL,8,FMiss Eastick was repeatedly assaulted
OL,9,Fover a period of some days and that
OL,10,Fthese assaults took place in the
OL,11,Fdefendant's flat. He, we say, is
OL,12,Fresponsible for her death and he meant
OL,13,Feither to kill her or cause her really
OL,14,Fserious harm and she died as a result
OL,15,Fof that harm."
OL,17,FMr Glenser said specialist evidence
OL,18,Findicates Melissa's bone fractures
OL,19,Fwere inflicted at different times,
OL,20,F"separated by days".
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G10/16
